doc.after: The European Union does not have one unified military The predecessors of the European Union were not devised as a strong military alliance because NATO was largely seen as appropriate and sufficient for defence purposes 130 22 EU members are members of NATO 131 while the remaining member states follow policies of neutrality 132 The Western European Union a military alliance with a mutual defence clause was disbanded in 2010 as its role had been transferred to the EU 133
